Rating: 4
Not only impressive presentation but also delicious! Made this for Easter Dinner and everyone loved it! Don't be afraid to make the parmesan custards the day before. I needed to double the recipe and did not have enough ramekins so I used a cupcake tin. After letting them cool (I left them right in the tin), I covered them with plastic wrap and refrigerated. To reheat, I put them back in the oven at 350 degrees for about 10 min in the hot water bath. I was able to gently lift them out of the cupcake tin with a thin rubber spatula without any difficulty - they stayed intact. Also made the soup the night before but only change I made to the soup was just before serving, to add evaporated milk instead of heavy cream, but first I thickened the evap milk as you would a cream sauce - with a Tbsp melted butter and Tbsp flour. Whisk a little soup into the cream sauce before adding it to the soup, then whisk the sauce into the soup. May sound complicated but it is not; the taste of the soup combined with the silky texture of the custard is worth it! Enjoy!

